reviews.text: It‚Äôs survived all the economic cycles of Reno and is still standing tall. The kids love this pizza and parents do too! The crust is perfectly light and fluffy. I find the college aged staff to be exceptionally nice and welcoming which is not common in today‚Äôs dining landscape.

Got a sausage pepperoni pizza.... domino's tastes better.  Used to like this place.  Tomatoes paste for sauce,  raw pepperoni, and 8 little sausage balls on extra large.  Really has fast food pizza flavor.
We love going to JJ's when we are in Reno. Get the JJ's Special. It's the best!  Casual environment. Excellent pizza (I like their dough because it's not sweet..just a normal yummy crust).

JJ‚Äôs has been around for as long as I can remember‚Ä¶ we used to have our little league post game pizza parties (ie parents have earned those beers!) back when I was in elementary school!  They‚Äôve changed little in the operation, and for good reason!  If it ain‚Äôt broke, don‚Äôt fix it!   The pizzas have always been delicious, I think it may be they they introduced me to my first Hawaiian pizza‚Ä¶ a deeply polarizing fare of which I stand firmly on the side if truth, life, liberty and the pursuit of happiness - provided that happiness includes Canadian bacon and canned pineapples.  Probably the most unique feature and unmistakably delicious yet totally out of left field anachronistic pizza choice (that is until you‚Äôve tried it!) is the serving of a side of honey - yes, the one and the same liquid bee magical elixir - and which seasoned customers will know and do  school the non-initiated into utilizing‚Ä¶ is meant for you to use at the END of the ingesting of a delicious slice of JJ‚Äôs Pie, wherein one takes the crust and dips it into the honey and those last few bites of scrumptious baked pizza dough suddenly becomes the dessert you never knew you needed so badly and just at that specific moment‚Ä¶ Tuesday's are a buy one 16‚Äù pizza and get a 10‚Äù pizza for free!  If interested in renting out the back room for your group event say a Little League team baseball post game parental inebriation party‚Ä¶ Be sure to hit them up on their website or give them a call to inquire about it‚Äôs availability. Otherwise just go and get some damn fine pizza, tasty wings or even a hot sub sandwich‚Ä¶ don‚Äôt worry, anything and everything there is sure to be delicious!   An original Reno restaurant serving our community and the surrounding area since 1983!

detailedReviews.author: John Stewart
detailedReviews.text:
I went to JJ's for the first time in 2021 while visiting Reno for the first time. I remember thinking, why am I having one of the best slices I've ever had in Reno, Nevada? But there I was, adding it to my Google maps as "best pizza ever."

3 years later, I came back to Reno and had to get try it again. I can not recommend it enough. It's delicious, the people are friendly and accommodating, and the only negative thing I can say is that I don't live close enough to grab a pie more often.

Keep it up, JJ's. I a-dough you.
